The paper analyzes in-text citations in scientific articles, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as the study involves analyzing a large dataset of scientific articles. The second likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as the study involves analyzing the characteristics of citations within text. The third likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the study involves analyzing the language used in scientific articles. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), as the study involves analyzing the behavior of researchers in the scientific community. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the study involves analyzing the relationships between scientific articles through citations.
